rComments: He is a great guy and I must say I was worried based on the previous rate my prof comments. But the class was chill. Despite the grading scheme was rigid, he was always available to discuss the matter. You definitely need to search outside of the lecture content to get full details. If you done PHS & ANP you will be prepared for this class

The 2 assignments were fair and he gives 24 hours for the open-book final exam. He always answers emails and provides good feedback. His notes could be a bit more clear but not horrible and he always asks for advice to better his teaching and the course. This course is very difficult but easy to succeed if you are willing to work hard.
His PowerPoint slides are terrible. The writing is very small. You have to bring computer just for his lectures to magnify the slides. Ridiculous.

Important to note that this class is taught by many professors/Doctors, not just Dr. Booth. The class itself is very interesting if you are interested in the biochemical side of diagnostic medicine. One midterm and one final, both open book, but the grading is very strict. Some of Dr. Booth's lectures are all over the map. Overall a good class.

He talks fast, gives a list of concepts, without making connection between them. Midterm was terrible. He tested things that we have never talked about, and he refused to provide marking rubric when students requested. He does not reply to emails either.
